Go on the NESdev page, and found the doccument that contains the pinout for NES ROM chips.<br />Then compare with the pinout of your EPROM. You should notice the difference, and then conclude the rewiring to do.<br />Btw, what is the difference between SAROM and SKROM ? SAROM isn't capabloe of high CHRROM sizes, right ? I think it is just like SKROM with less pinholes in the board and designed for smallest CHR size, where the ROMs have the same pinout as EPROM ? If it is that, you won't need to rewire your EPROM at all, unless it has more pins that what the board allows.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Fri May 12, 2006 8:52 am</p><hr />
